IMAGE
An image and a container runtime (Docker engine) are needed to create a container
 # an image is like a blueprint or template, and the building material, while a container is an instance of that blueprint or template.
 #  The image provides all the necessary instructions and dependencies for the container to run. 
 # A Docker image is a file. An image never changes; you can not edit an existing file. 
 # Creating a new image happens by starting from a base image and adding new layers to it. 
* docker image ls #list all image
 This image file is built from an instructional file named Dockerfile that is parsed when you run docker image build run:
 (syntax) * docker buildx build [OPTIONS] PATH | URL |
